ownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532530\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532530\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tut1665702663138.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tut1665702663138.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tut1665702663138.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tut1665702663138\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Retrieval\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tut1665702663138__data_retrieval_134977\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Every DBMS connector recognizes the same set of connector I/O requests. When retrieving data from the database, Uniface selects the required data with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Select</span> connector request, and fetches it into the component with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Fetch</span> connector request. Uniface uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Select</span> request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tut1665702663138__p_d43598e1_d43599e1_d43600e1\">The most commonly used connector I/O requests include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tut1665702663138__li_d21764e1_d21765e1_d21766e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lcg1665702663207.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lcg1665702663207.html\" title=\"Select records or rows matching a profile.\">S Select</a>—select a group of occurrences that match the retrieve profile: it can include wildcards. The connector returns the hitlist, possibly in steps, and can return data if the select cache can be used.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tut1665702663138__li_d21767e1_d21768e1_d21769e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iqo1665702663424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iqo1665702663424.html\" title=\"Fetch one record or row.\">F Fetch</a>—return the data for a single occurrence. If necessary, the connector interface includes a mode indicating that the occurrence should be locked.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tut1665702663138__li_d21770e1_d21771e1_d21772e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"roe1665702663498.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/roe1665702663498.html\" title=\"Update existing record or row.\">U Update</a>—update the data for an existing occurrence in the DBMS.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tut1665702663138__li_d21773e1_d21774e1_d21775e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wby1665702663634.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wby1665702663634.html\" title=\"Write or insert one record or row.\">W Write</a>—insert a new occurrence into the DBMS.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tut1665702663138__li_d21776e1_d21777e1_d21778e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yyx1665702663704.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yyx1665702663704.html\" title=\"Delete existing record or row.\">D Delete</a>—delete an existing occurrence from the DBMS.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tut1665702663138__p_d43601e1_d43602e1_d43603e1\">When retrieving data from a DBMS, Uniface uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Select</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Fetch</span> connector I/O requests to locate the desired database occurrences and to bring the data into the component. When a request is made for data, either by the user or by a ProcScript instruction, the connector interface issues the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Select</span> request. The DBMS connector responds to this request by locating the requested occurrences in the database, using the retrieve profile as the argument.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tut1665702663138__p_d43604e1_d43605e1_d43606e1\">If no matching occurrence is found, the retrieve process stops and no more calls are made to the DBMS connector in the current attempt to retrieve data. If only one occurrence is found, Uniface sends a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Fetch</span> request to the DBMS connector to bring that occurrence into the form.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spb1665702919328.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Connector Requests</a><p>Database connector requests are recognized by every Uniface DBMS connector. Each request is identified by an alphabetic character, such as O for Open or S for Select. You need to know these requests and the modes that some of them use, when analyzing I/O messages in the message frame.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532530\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532530\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Retrieval Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Retrieval Every DBMS connector recognizes the same set of connector I/O requests. When retrieving data from the database, Uniface selects the required data with the Select connector request, and fetches it into the component with the Fetch connector request. Uniface uses the Select request to create a partially built hitlist called a stepped hitlist. The most commonly used connector I/O requests include: S Select —select a group of occurrences that match the retrieve profile: it can include wildcards. The connector returns the hitlist, possibly in steps, and can return data if the select cache can be used. F Fetch —return the data for a single occurrence. If necessary, the connector interface includes a mode indicating that the occurrence should be locked. U Update —update the data for an existing occurrence in the DBMS. W Write —insert a new occurrence into the DBMS. D Delete —delete an existing occurrence from the DBMS. When retrieving data from a DBMS, Uniface uses the Select and Fetch connector I/O requests to locate the desired database occurrences and to bring the data into the component. When a request is made for data, either by the user or by a ProcScript instruction, the connector interface issues the Select request. The DBMS connector responds to this request by locating the requested occurrences in the database, using the retrieve profile as the argument. If no matching occurrence is found, the retrieve process stops and no more calls are made to the DBMS connector in the current attempt to retrieve data. If only one occurrence is found, Uniface sends a Fetch request to the DBMS connector to bring that occurrence into the form. Related Links Database Connector Requests Database connector requests are recognized by every Uniface DBMS connector. Each request is identified by an alphabetic character, such as O for Open or S for Select. You need to know these requests and the modes that some of them use, when analyzing I/O messages in the message frame. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}